# Memory And Audit Hot Spots

- In `build-rolling-memory.ts`, de-duping should keep the most specific fact, not the shortest paraphrase.
- In `build-rolling-memory.ts`, only clear `mustNotKnowYet` when a single `knows` entry fully covers the forbidden fact's meaningful tokens; loose overlap is not enough.
- Keep `activeTraits`, `dialogueHabits`, and `tabooNotes` semantically separate when merging voice data.
- Do not map generic `voiceNotes` directly into `tabooNotes`.
- Any synthesized voice card should carry a valid `updatedFromChapter`.
- In final-audit flow, blocking decisions should follow the audit contract consistently, not ad hoc status/string heuristics.
- `POST_FIX_WORD_COUNT` is advisory-only and must not flip audit blocking by itself.
- `mergeAuditWithValidator` must tag every issue with `source: "model" | "validator"` so the fix-loop can distinguish them.
- Validator-only blocking (every error-severity issue has `source: "validator"`) must downgrade to warnings via `downgradeValidatorOnlyErrors` rather than trigger the wholesale `fixContinuity` rewrite. The deterministic validators are too false-positive-prone to overrule a literary-judge-approved chapter.
- Publish-candidate immutability: snapshot the prose entering final audit. The publish-candidate ratchet runs BEFORE the post-fix `BLOCKED_QUALITY` threshold gate. Revert when EITHER the post-fix re-judge regresses beyond `qualitySettings.publishCandidateRegressionTolerance` OR the post-fix drops below `qualitySettings.judgePassThreshold` while the candidate had cleared it (otherwise a sub-tolerance nudge under threshold would block a publishable candidate). On revert: restore prose, review, delta, memory, and audit, downgrade any blocking errors on the restored candidate to warnings via `downgradeAllErrorsToWarnings` (preserves `source`), annotate the summary via `annotateRevertedAuditSummary`, and publish. Use `shouldRevertToPublishCandidate` for both the tolerance and threshold comparisons (pass `passThreshold` + `postFixPassesThreshold`). Do NOT force-set `source: "validator"` on the revert path — it destroys operator-visible provenance.
- `PARAGRAPH_DISTRIBUTION` is warning-only forever. Do not promote it to error severity.
- `INVERTED_NP_CONTRAST`, `WITHHOLDING_TIC`, and `EXPLANATORY_BECAUSE_CLUSTER` in `src/validators/prose-quality.ts` are warning-only narration-only detectors. They run after `stripDialogueForNarration` and use partly-predictive seed lists; sharpen the lists or regex rather than lowering thresholds when calibrating.
- If you touch these areas, add or update a focused regression test in `tests/runtime-safety.test.ts`.
